title: Zena Latto
summary: Zena Latto (October 25, 1925 – April 5, 2016) was an American jazz clarinetist and saxophonist.  During the 1940s and 1950s, she played with the big band the International Sweethearts of Rhythm. She purchased a baritone saxophone to stay with that group and continued to perform with the Sweethearts until 1955. Latto performed with her own band the Modern Moods from 1955 to 1957.
